FYI if you play this in VLC, when the audio goes out of sync just adjust it as follows:
click 'tools', then 'preferences', then at the bottom left-hand side change 'show settings' to 'all', then 'audio', you can now advance or retard the audio over video where it says 'audio desynchronisation compensation'.  You can change it in miliseconds + or -  I have used this a few times and it will bring the movie back into sync.  You will need to play around with the timings until you get it right though.  Good luck.
